import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    values = data['values']
    plt.hist(values, bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of volcano eruption values?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['width'] = pd.to_numeric(data['width'], errors='coerce')
    data['height'] = pd.to_numeric(data['height'], errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['width'], data['height'])
    plt.xlabel('Width')
    plt.ylabel('Height')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between the width and height of volcano eruptions?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    unique_values = data['values'].nunique()
    value_counts = data['values'].value_counts()
    if len(value_counts) > 20:
        value_counts = value_counts[:20]
    ax = value_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('Unique Values')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of unique volcano eruption values?', wrap=True)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    ax.axvline(x=unique_values, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Unique Values: {unique_values:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['height'] = data['height'].astype(int)
    data['values'] = data['values'].astype(int)
    plt.hist(data['values'], bins=20, alpha=0.5, label='Values', stacked=True)
    plt.xlabel('Height')
    plt.ylabel('Values')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of volcano eruption values by height?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
